    {
      "unresolved": true,
      "key": {
        "uuid": "b2292473_6a6d80fc",
        "filename": "src/chromiumos/tast/cmd/tast-lint/main.go",
        "patchSetId": 2
      },
      "lineNbr": 372,
      "author": {
        "id": 1512082
      },
      "writtenOn": "2021-05-27T08:32:39Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "hi, cmd.Output() captures only stdout. The returned error is not elaborative (something like `exit status \u003cstatuscode\u003e`). The detailed error can be captured either by attaching a stderr buffer before the command execution or by using cmd.CombinedOutput(). I try to avoid the later one 😄",
      "parentUuid": "4b84bad2_5c47a9da",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 372,
        "startChar": 1,
        "endLine": 372,
        "endChar": 24
      },
      "revId": "a14a864f30e648e7867b61f4f6dfcd7a6ed6c49f",
      "serverId": "3ce6091f-6c88-37e8-8c75-72f92ae8dfba"
    },
    {
      "unresolved": false,
      "key": {
        "uuid": "6792c6ca_9c29c488",
        "filename": "src/chromiumos/tast/cmd/tast-lint/main.go",
        "patchSetId": 2
      },
      "lineNbr": 372,
      "author": {
        "id": 1306673
      },
      "writtenOn": "2021-05-27T14:10:07Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "Due to the documentation Output() usually returns exec.ExitError which contains Stderr if command stderr was nil:\nhttps://golang.org/pkg/os/exec/#Cmd.Output\n\nHere are some use cases in Tast codebase:\nhttps://source.chromium.org/search?q\u003dtast-tests%20exec.ExitError\n\nOTOH it looks a bit complicated, so let\u0027s keep existing approach.",
      "parentUuid": "b2292473_6a6d80fc",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 372,
        "startChar": 1,
        "endLine": 372,
        "endChar": 24
      },
